@startuml
title EcommerceApp AWS Setup

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

cloud "AWS" {
  frame "Region: us-east-2" {
    package "VPC\n10.0.0.0/16" as VPC {
      rectangle "Internet Gateway" as IGW

      package "Public Subnets" {
        rectangle "Public Subnet One\n10.0.1.0/24" as PublicSubnetOne
        rectangle "Public Subnet Two\n10.0.2.0/24" as PublicSubnetTwo
      }

      package "Private Subnets" {
        rectangle "Private Subnet One\n10.0.3.0/24" as PrivateSubnetOne
        rectangle "Private Subnet Two\n10.0.4.0/24" as PrivateSubnetTwo
      }

      rectangle "Public Route Table\n0.0.0.0/0 -> IGW" as PublicRouteTable
      rectangle "Private Route Table" as PrivateRouteTable

      node "EC2 Instance\nweb_instance" as EC2
      rectangle "Security Group\n80, 22, 443 from 0.0.0.0/0" as SG
    }

    package "IAM" {
      rectangle "IAM Policy\nexample_policy" as Policy
      rectangle "IAM Role\nexample_role" as Role
      rectangle "Instance Profile\nexample_profile" as Profile
    }
  }
}

VPC --> IGW : attached

PublicSubnetOne --> PublicRouteTable : associated
PublicSubnetTwo --> PublicRouteTable : associated
PrivateSubnetOne --> PrivateRouteTable : associated
PrivateSubnetTwo --> PrivateRouteTable : associated

PublicRouteTable --> IGW : default route

EC2 --> PublicSubnetOne : deployed in
EC2 --> SG : uses
EC2 --> Profile : attached

Profile --> Role : contains
Role --> Policy : attached

note right of PublicRouteTable
  Public subnets have internet access
  through the Internet Gateway.
end note

note right of PrivateRouteTable
  No NAT gateway is defined.
  Private subnets have no outbound
  internet route in this setup.
end note

@enduml
